<P>
   &QL; 
JAIL-PORN _ In a rare move, a federal appeals court reversed
another appellate ruling Tuesday, upholding a ban on Playboy and
other sexually explicit materials at Maricopa County jails. The 7-4
vote by the 9th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals said the regulation,
imposed in 1993 by Sheriff Joe Arpaio, reasonably ensures jail
safety without violating inmates' First Amendment rights. By JERRY
KAMMER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL;
