<HEADLINE>
SUSPENSIONS MEAN M'S `HAVE TO JUGGLE' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By DAN RALEY  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO _ Let the Mariners roster shuffle begin.
</P>
<P>
   American League officials Tuesday upheld Frankie Rodriguez's
seven-day suspension, effective immediately, and shortened Jay
Buhner's four-day penalty to three, beginning Aug. 25, for their
roles in two separate fights.
</P>
<P>
   The action comes one day after appeals hearings were conducted
in SkyDome. Counting reliever Jose Paniagua's recently concluded
five-game punishment, the Mariners will have to play short-handed
for 15 of 16 contests.
</P>
<P>
   ``What it amounts to is we're going to have to juggle for the
next 10 days,'' manager Lou Piniella said.
</P>
