<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 13:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1456 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r e BC-JAMES-BOND-HNS &LR;      08-18 0575
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JAMES-BOND-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRING BACK THE POLITICALLY INCORRECT 007 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By TERRY NORTON  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANSELMO, Calif. _ The sense and sensibilities of American
life, as if they aren't under enough attack by our infamous
politicos, have suffered another blow at the hands of Hollywood's
power mongers.
</P>
<P>
   The political correctness police think they've hit pay dirt, but
all I see is a horny feminist's nightmare. I'm suddenly longing for
the old days.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe you've already heard. James Bond has quit smoking.
</P>
<P>
   As a life-long advocate for women's equality, I'd like to go on
record as reclaiming our God-given right to drool over nasty hunks
in our little dark, anonymous, creaky, loge-seat corner of the
world.
</P>
<P>
   By the light of day, sure, we want equal pay, hands off,
respect, promotions and a shot at the presidency. But by night,
there's a bit of Barbarella in all of us.
</P>
<P>
   We may be headed for the top of the ladder, but we still like
bad boys. We don't want their hands down our blouses, we don't want
them near the Oval Office (too late), but on celluloid, what can
they hurt?
</P>
<P>
   Where's the harm in lusting for an insensitive gorgeous
super-hero once in a while as long as he's a caricature? We want
manly old-fashioned movie heroes. The retro guy. Pouting,
trash-talking and obtuse, so we can snicker about him afterwards.
We want him to ride untamed horses while lustily drawing on an
unfiltered cigarette, chasing busty Italian women named Sophia, so
we can tsk-tsk into our popcorn.
</P>
<P>
   We want bad boys who paint naked women gold and make plans to
blow up the world while sipping martinis served by scantily clad
beauties. We want women who purr for men so we can slap our thighs
and say thank God we've come a long way, baby. We want hot sex,
half-naked men and wantonness with a capital ``W.'' And we're
willing to pay $7.50.
</P>
<P>
   You know who we're going to get now? James Bond, the sissy. A
drip who's worried about his cholesterol, ordering Caesar salad
with his dressing on the side. A dork who's in bed by 10. Alone.
</P>
<P>
   Next thing we know, he'll be quoting Kahlil Gibran. He'll be
moisturizing when he should be womanizing and meditating when he
should be dancing the midnight grind. What next, celibacy?
</P>
<P>
   A church-going James Bond just isn't going to excite us.
</P>
<P>
   Hollywood might as well forget Pierce Brosnan and cast George
Bush.
</P>
<P>
   We don't want to hear, ``May I introduce myself? The name's Bond
and I'm a member of NOW. Can I offer you a cranberry Calistoga?''
</P>
<P>
   We want straight shots and hot pants. We want gorgeous, smart,
seductive women pitted against testosterone-laden, scotch-slamming,
breast-hungry heroes.
</P>
<P>
   Movies are where we go to escape the idiocy of life as we not
only know it, but live it every day. We desperately need a fantasy
life where everything isn't kosher pickles.
</P>
<P>
   We crave exaggeration and superlatives. We require them to get
past all the '90s rules and mores we so ardently follow 24-7.
</P>
<P>
   When we go to the show, we want Thunderpussies _ not wimps.
</P>
<P>
   I say let James Bond wend his way to lung cancer while his
former co-star Pussy Galore chokes on secondhand smoke. Leave the
obnoxious purity to the audience. We'll handle it on our end.
</P>
<P>
   God knows we're not allowed to do anything else these days.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Terry Norton is a free-lance writer who lives in Marin County,
Calif.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-18-99 1322EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
