   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ POTEAU MOUNTAIN, Okla. _ I am standing in this
mountain valley before this huge rock in the exact same spot where
a Norse Viking named Glome stood nearly 1,400 years ago. Glome
painstakingly etched an inscription on this billboard-size rock in
Old Norse runes, which are alphabet characters formerly used by
ancient Europeans. Columbus, who never set foot in North America,
has parades in his honor in American cities while Glome and his
pre-Columbian Norsemen buddies were carving ``No trespassing''
signs on rocks in eastern Oklahoma hundreds of years before
Columbus was born. Some people can't catch a break. (Nethaway, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
