   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   GUNS-NEXTDOOR _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Do you know whether or not there
are guns in the home of your child's playmate? With school
shootings seemingly in the headlines every month, and a growing
awareness of the dangers of children and guns, more parents are
adding gun safety to their list of concerns. There are a multitude
of worries parents can have when their children are playing at
someone else's home, but this one is particularly scary. (Santos,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CHRISTENING-GIFTS _ Christening gowns destined to become
heirlooms. We take a look a what's out there, what are the fabrics,
what they cost, etc. Tips on preserving these gowns. Also, sidebar
on christening gifts with emphasis on heirloom items like silver
spoons, tiny white Bibles, etc. (Johnson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-GUIDE _ A weekly feature telling how to locate
hard-to-fnd items. This week: Maja soap, fruit jellies, powdered
vanilla, Heinz ketchup in a glass bottle, Bumble and bumble hair
care products and Easy Wash laundry stain remover. (Johnson,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-DESTINATION _ A weekly feature about fun places to shop
in the Southeast. This week: Mall of Georgia near Buford. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDS: Moving on l (Lifestyle) and a (General News) categories.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-JAMS _ Even if their grandmothers shunned it in favor of
convenient commercial products, a younger generation is reviving
the art of canning; witness the surge in sales of canning jars. If
you've never done it before, jams and jellies is a good place to
start -- it involves less costly equipment and poses less risk,
plus you can exercise your creativity creating flavor combos
unfound on supermarket shelves. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH COLOR PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-JAMS-RECIPES _ Recipe page to go with JAMS story
centerpieced on AJC weekly food section. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
