   COXNET WRESTLING PAGE
</P>
<P>
   The weekly CoxNet wrestling page is available Wednesday
afternoons by 5 p.m. EDT. Keying to the Monday wrestling events,
It's good for publication any day through Sunday. Here are the
elements on the page, which are also moving on the entertainment
wire:
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-SLAM _ Look ahead to WWF Summerslam PPV and Minnesota
Gov. Jesse Ventura's role. Should he be doing this, reports on net
that he is receiving more than the $100,000 he's giving to charity.
How will this effect his run for presidency? w/chart on predicted
outcomes
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-ROADWILD _ Look back at WCW's Road Wild PPV. Hogan is
in a 'career' match, if he loses his wrestling 'career' is over. It
looks like he may lose because he is struggling with a
hyperextended knee injury and needs the time off a loss would give
him. But will this happen? We'll know Sat. night. Also, WCW doesn't
travel well to Sturgis, many wrestlers took motorcycles and had
accidents and incidents on the way, so which could effect who
actually wrestles. This will probably be the last free (for the
fans in attendance) Road Wild for WCW. Combo with Bret Hart's
return to wrestling on Monday night nitro (to followup on our
should he stay, should he go story). (Allen, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-GETREAL _ Test, former Motley Crew body guard turned
wrestler and boyfriend of WWF owner's daughter. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-LOOKALIKE _ Kane, a.k.a. Diesel and Isaac Yankem.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-TOP10 _ We'll give an update and ask for more
responses. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE _ The British Bulldog is back in the WWF,
Taz inks 3-year deal with ECW and Raven may return to roost with
ECW. (Allen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
