   CIR-CELL (New York) _ While no one knows the precise number of
cell phone calls that are not completed, fade in and out or get cut
off midconversation, such incidents are increasingly common
complaints among wireless users. And they raise an important
question: As successful as wireless companies have been in
attracting subscribers, what are they doing to keep them happy? By
Catherine Greenman.
</P>
