<SLUG> BC-HOME-BUDGET-NYT </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Home Section stories from The N.Y. Times News Service for
Thursday, Aug. 19:
</P>
<P>
   CATSKILLS (Ellenville, N.Y.) _ Maybe it's the tiny glossy
photograph of the bowler hat and hatrack tacked to the wall of the
foyer. Maybe it's the amber plastic beads substituting for a door
to the funky aqua and white kitchen with the Italian molded chairs.
Or maybe it's the young woman with shingled hair, a graphic
designer/wire sculptor who wears her tank top and Dickies painter's
pants with elan and who has turned the old plastics factory here in
the Catskills into her personal retreat. Whatever it is, this is
not your grandmother's Catskills. By Tracie Rozhon.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   LONG-ISLAND-COTTAGE (Undated) _ They had gone out to Long Island
to see about a summer rental, and as soon as they saw the
cinder-block cottage in Springs, they fell for it. The weekly human
nature feature by Anne Raver.
</P>
<P>
   SWIMMING-POOL (Undated) _ ``Hold the chain saw _ I'm moving to
Florida!'' Daniel R. Lewis, an insurance heir, said just as
construction workers were revving up to add a $1 million indoor
swimming pool to his 8,000-square-foot house in suburban Cleveland.
Lewis, an insurance company director, had decided that the house
was simply not distinguished enough for the swimming pool he had in
mind. The Miami area was a much more natural fit. By Julie V.
Iovine.
</P>
