<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Can-do Brunswick stew simmers
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Marlene Brown's request for Brunswick Stew using all
canned ingredients brought a dozen similar replies. All called for
canned barbecue meats, vegetables, tomatoes and corn. A few added
cans of lima beans or okra. And some called for a chopped fresh
onion, deviating just a pinch from the all-canned requirement.
</P>
<P>
   The biggest difference, though, was in the cooking. Most called
for simply opening cans, stirring the mix and heating for 20 to 30
minutes. One went further _ to simmer an additional hour. But a
couple make use of the crockpot _ simmering the stew all day,
blending the flavors, so it is ready when you get home. Our tester
liked this slow-cooked one, sent by Alva Bentley of Decatur, Ga.,
and said it benefits from cooking the full eight hours.
</P>
<P>
   MAIN DISH
</P>
<P>
   Crockpot
</P>
<P>
   Brunswick Stew
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 cups
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: about 10 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 6-8 hours
</P>
<P>
   1 medium onion, finely chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 (28-ounce) can tomatoes, chopped (or two 16-ounce cans)
</P>
<P>
   1 (15-ounce) can Castleberry
</P>
<P>
   barbecue pork, beef or chicken
</P>
<P>
   1 (10-ounce) can Castleberry
</P>
<P>
   barbecue beef
</P>
<P>
   1 (10-ounce) can Swanson chicken
</P>
<P>
   1 (14 3/4-ounce) can creamed corn
</P>
<P>
   1 (15-ounce) can whole kernel shoe peg corn, drained
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup barbecue sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/2 to 1 teaspoon ground black
</P>
<P>
   pepper, or to taste
</P>
<P>
   1/2 tablespoon salt, or to taste
</P>
<P>
   1/2 tablespoon granulated sugar,
</P>
<P>
   or to taste
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon vinegar or
</P>
<P>
   lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   Place all ingredients in the crockpot and stir to combine. Cook
on low for 6 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
</P>
<P>
   Per cup (with 1/2 tablespoon salt): 344 calories, 30 grams
protein, 8 grams fat (percent calories from fat, 21), 41 grams
carbohydrates, 76 milligrams cholesterol, 1,468 milligrams sodium,
3 grams fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Contacting this column
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests for this column
</P>
<P>
   should be sent to Recipe Swap, Food Department, The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution,
</P>
<P>
   P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Include a daytime telephone
number. E-mail: mlanghenry(at)ajc.com.
</P>
<P>
   Where to write
</P>
<P>
   Send food news to Food Department, The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. The
deadline is noon two Mondays before publication.
</P>
<P>
   Editor: Susan Puckett at spuckett(at)ajc.com.
</P>
<P>
   404-526-5443.
</P>
<P>
   Assistant editor: Marcia Langhenry at mlanghenry(at)ajc.com.
404-526-5418.
</P>
<P>
   Food and nutrition writer: Reagan Walker at rwalker(at)ajc.com.
404-526-5856.
</P>
<P>
   Food writer/dining critic: John Kessler at jkessler(at)ajc.com.
404-526-5452.
</P>
