   DEMS-VALUES (Washington) _ Every few months, small groups of
local Democratic officials journey to special seminars to learn how
to think and talk about their values. Under the auspices of the
Democratic Leadership Council, they learn to stop speaking in the
numbing language of program names and acronyms. That the council
feels the need to run such seminars says something about a
persistent difficulty facing Democrats as they head into the next
election: strategists say the public once again sees the
Republicans as the party of values. By Alison Mitchell.
