 &HT;    Store lineup: Try this on for size
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Shopping Destination: The Mall of Georgia
</P>
<P>
   It's the mall to beat all. After two years in the making, the
mammoth Mall of Georgia _ the biggest in the state _ has opened
with much fanfare on 500 acres near Buford on Ga. 20 at I-85 (Exit
46). The mall, with its 1.7 million square feet of retail space,
aims to be a regional draw, bringing millions of shoppers and
dollars to Gwinnett County. Despite its size, developers want the
mall to have a small-town warmth, and many of its features attempt
to evoke images of bygone Main Streets. Three anchor department
stores _ Dillard's, J.C. Penney and Lord &AMP; Taylor _ are open.
Nordstrom is expected to open next spring; Rich's, next fall. About
100 of the 150 retail slots for smaller stores are filled, and the
remainder will open over the next several months. Here's a look at
the store lineup. Information: 678-482-8788.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
