<HEADLINE>
(ATTN: PA.)  
 UNIVERSAL NAMES MISHER NEW HEAD OF PRODUCTION  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
   By THE NEW YORK TIMES   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOLLYWOOD _ In a move likely to surprise no one in the movie
business, Kevin Misher was elevated Tuesday to president of
production for Universal Pictures, making him responsible for the
studio's feature film output.
</P>
<P>
   Misher's promotion from his previous job as Universal's
co-president of production ends an executive shuffling set in
motion by the ouster of Frank Biondi Jr., the former studio
chairman, and Casey Silver, the former head of production.
</P>
<P>
   The dismissal of Silver on Nov. 30 resulted in the departure of
the last top Universal executive; his tenure dated from before the
purchase of the company by the Seagram Co..
</P>
<P>
   The appointment Tuesday was seen by many in Hollywood as giving
Edgar Bronfman Jr., Seagram's chief executive, a handpicked team in
the feature film division.
</P>
<P>
   ``What Bronfman is doing is creating a well-rounded artistic and
financial team,'' said Brian Grazer, whose Imagine Entertainment
has produced numerous films with Universal, including
``Bowfinger,'' starring Steve Martin and Eddie Murphy.
</P>
<P>
   Misher, 34, graduated from the Wharton School of the University
of Pennsylvania in 1987, joined Tri-Star Pictures as a production
executive in 1990 and moved to Universal in 1996.
</P>
<P>
   At Universal, he has been associated with films like ``Patch
Adams,'' a hit that he was credited with having rescued from limbo,
repackaging it with Robin Williams as the star.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
