<HEADLINE>
MOVIES: ``BOWFINGER'' 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By KARI BRASSELERO, 10th Grade Student Reporter 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``BOWFINGER''
</P>
<P>
   Starring: Steve Martin, Eddie Murphy, Heather Graham, Jamie
Kennedy, Christine Baranski and Robert Downey Jr.
</P>
<P>
   Plot: Bobby Bowfinger, an aspiring movie producer (and a
schemer, a liar and an all-around crude guy) recruits a bunch of
odd but likable losers to help him trick the biggest name in movies
to star in his super-low-budget film.
</P>
<P>
   Comments: Very original script with an absolutely hilarious
performance by Eddie Murphy, who plays two roles: Kit Ramsey, a
Hollywood action star with a big ego and his brother, Jiff Ramsey,
who is sweet but kind of nerdy.
</P>
<P>
   Also fantastic was Steve Martin, who wrote the screenplay for
this comedy and plays Bowfinger. By the way, Martin was born in
Waco, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Heather Graham, seen this summer in ``Austin Powers: The Spy Who
Shagged Me,'' appears as Daisy, an actress newly arrived in
Hollywood from the Midwest who pins her hopes of being a movie star
on Bowfinger. And Downey plays Jerry Renfro, a hot-shot movie
studio executive who reads Bowfinger's film script.
</P>
<P>
   Rating and reason for rating: PG-13 for offensive language, sex
scenes and sexual innuendo.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 rating: 8.
</P>
