<HEADLINE>
MUSIC: PAUL BRANDT'S CD, ``THAT'S THE TRUTH'' 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By DENYSE REBER, 9th Grade Student Reporter 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CD ``THAT'S THE TRUTH''
</P>
<P>
   Artist: Paul Brandt.
</P>
<P>
   Country music: Either you love it or you hate it. Well, listen
to one song by Paul Brandt and you'll start to love it.
</P>
<P>
   This is the fourth album by Brandt, whose hometown is Calgary,
in the province of Alberta, Canada. The first album, ``Calm Before
the Storm,'' was released in March 1996.
</P>
<P>
   His new CD is real fun, blending rock and pop with country. He
has a smooth voice. Watch out Garth Brooks, you might have some
competition. I think this guy will be popping the charts with this
CD.
</P>
<P>
   The CD includes songs such as ``that's the Truth,'' ``There's a
World Out There'' and a nice mellow tune, ``The Sycamore Tree.''
</P>
<P>
   It's a really good CD. And that's the truth.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 rating: 8.
