<HEADLINE>
THE BLOBIFICATION OF MODERN DESIGN
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Novelist  &UR; Tom Wolfe &LR; , who between novels wrote books critical of
modern painting and architecture, considers the state of design and
bangs his walking stick on the floor in the latest issue of Men's
Journal.
</P>
<P>
   Citing such titans of design as  &UR; Raymond Loewy &LR;  (whose credits
include the Studebaker and Postal Service eagle) and  &UR; Harley Earl &LR; 
(General Motors cars), Wolfe complains about today's designers of
`` `blobjets,' roundish, childish blob-like objects that now come
in every form from the iMac computer to the Mazda Miata, the Ford
Taurus and the reborn Volkswagen Beetle. These objects are not
meant to be exuberant, much less elegant. The key adjective is
childish.''
</P>
<P>
   Wolfe names names. ``The art world's idea of a great designer is
the Frenchman  &UR; Philippe Starck &LR; ,'' whose interiors, says Wolfe,
look like backdrops for male models, ``the ones with the eight-day
growth of beard, the hangdog slouch and the glum look of a
recovering codeine addict who just flunked out of his 12-step
program. ...
</P>
<P>
   ``In a worshipful piece, the New York Times named him one of the
giants of 20th century design and said his work `revolves around
fear of rejection.' Marvelous.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ANSEL ADAMS FIND &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Ten  &UR; Ansel Adams &LR;  photos of San Francisco's then-new Grace
Cathedral, taken perhaps in the mid-'40s, have been discovered in
the cathedral basement, where they had been stored _ and forgotten
_ 40 years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Cherie Dunn, who's on the cathedral's Art Council, says the
group hopes to display the photos for the congregation's 150th
anniversary, in December.
</P>
<P>
   Before that, however, they're in need of proper museum-quality
framing, which (along with insurance) will cost somewhere between
$3,000 and $5,000. Grace is looking for an Adams angel.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Designer  &UR; Paco Rabanne &LR; , who predicted that the Mir space
station would destroy Paris during last week's eclipse, told the
Times of London, ``I am sorry. But I am still convinced that Paris
will be hit by a dramatic happening.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Sharon Stone &LR;  told Movieline magazine that she ``didn't
appreciate''  &UR; Gwyneth Paltrow &LR; 's parody of her on ``Saturday Night
Live,'' but she thinks it came out of naivete rather than malicious
intent. ``She's very young,'' said Stone of Paltrow, ``and lives in
rarefied air that's a little thin. It's like she's not getting
quite enough oxygen. ... I would like to think that she will
eventually spend her fame valuably.
</P>
<P>
   ``The women in the generation before me cut the path for women
like me to walk freely in the world. The women in this next
generation don't really know what that cost. So they don't respect
it.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Robert Duvall &LR;  will direct and star in ``Assassination
Tango,'' which W describes as a movie about ``a dashing hit man who
gets hooked on tango while in Argentina on a mission.''
</P>
<P>
   _ KKSF music director  &UR; Blake Lawrence &LR;  is hiding under his desk,
having received word, from GTSO Records, that  &UR; John Tesh &LR; 's version
of  &UR; Ricky Martin &LR; 's ``Livin' La Vida Loca'' is coming.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SNIFFING WITH YOUR DOG &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DeAnn Lowell &LR; , founder of Peppermint Pets, explains why an
adjustable cotton collar stuffed with a blend of herbs is a good
idea for both human- and dogwear: ``Our ancestors were very
familiar with the physical and emotional benefits of aromatic
plants and oils. Much of what they learned about aroma therapy,
they picked up by watching animals in nature. ... The fragrance of
our collars promotes an emotionally balanced and calm environment
for pets and people, so we can both be more actualized.''
</P>
<P>
   And if you can't understand why you would want to be
``actualized,'' the company provides some hard facts you might want
to mention at a dinner party: ``If the densely packed olfactory
membrane in the canine nose was laid out in a single layer, it
would cover an area equal to over 65 percent of the dog's body
size'' (or an eensy weensy portion of the state of New Jersey).
``By comparison, the olfactory membrane in a human nose is about
the size of a postage stamp.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I felt sorry for Jimmy because I think he fell in love with me
a little bit during the film. You know, there's a lot of hugging
that goes on in mob films, and I started to get the impression that
his hugs were lasting a little longer than they need to. ... Then
the poems started. ... Anyway, he's through it and moved on.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Hugh Grant in ``facetious mode,'' said his Movie magazine
interviewer Andrea Chase, describing his relationship with ``Mickey
Blue Eyes'' co-star James Caan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
