station would destroy Paris during last week's eclipse, told the
Times of London, ``I am sorry. But I am still convinced that Paris
will be hit by a dramatic happening.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Sharon Stone &LR;  told Movieline magazine that she ``didn't
appreciate''  &UR; Gwyneth Paltrow &LR; 's parody of her on ``Saturday Night
Live,'' but she thinks it came out of naivete rather than malicious
intent. ``She's very young,'' said Stone of Paltrow, ``and lives in
rarefied air that's a little thin. It's like she's not getting
quite enough oxygen. ... I would like to think that she will
eventually spend her fame valuably.
</P>
<P>
   ``The women in the generation before me cut the path for women
like me to walk freely in the world. The women in this next
generation don't really know what that cost. So they don't respect
it.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Robert Duvall &LR;  will direct and star in ``Assassination
Tango,'' which W describes as a movie about ``a dashing hit man who
gets hooked on tango while in Argentina on a mission.''
</P>
