   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I felt sorry for Jimmy because I think he fell in love with me
a little bit during the film. You know, there's a lot of hugging
that goes on in mob films, and I started to get the impression that
his hugs were lasting a little longer than they need to. ... Then
the poems started. ... Anyway, he's through it and moved on.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Hugh Grant in ``facetious mode,'' said his Movie magazine
interviewer Andrea Chase, describing his relationship with ``Mickey
Blue Eyes'' co-star James Caan.
</P>
