<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ As Gov. George W. Bush crisscrosses the country
in his bid for the White House, he is being targeted back home by
lawsuits that could wind up as fodder for political opponents. In
one case, the controversy surrounding Bush's 1960s-era service in
the Texas Air National Guard _ and questions about how he got in _
has become a subject of exploration. In another, Bush has been
subpoenaed to testify about a whistle-blower case involving a
politically connected funeral home company. By JAY ROOT. Story has
moved in ``p'' political category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
