<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Aug. 19 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   PENNIES-CRUNCH (Los Angeles) _ Wells Fargo Bank is having a hard
time getting its hands on cash. Pennies, specifically. The San
Francisco-based bank was going to award one million pennies _ along
with a number of other prizes _ to its one-millionth Internet
customer, but can't scrape together enough copper. ``We can't get
one million pennies,'' said Kathy Shilkret, Wells spokeswoman.
Wells Fargo isn't alone. By Deborah Adamson. (Will move in the
``n'' California and ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
