NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, AUGUST 19
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-BUSH-CRIME-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Aug. 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Aug. 17,
about Gov. George W. Bush's record on crime misstated an editorial
position by The Houston Chronicle. The paper urged him to veto a
bill for public defenders, not to sign it.
</P>
<P>
   BC-AFTER-HOURS-TRADING-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Aug. 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Aug. 17,
about the teaming of ETrade Group, the on-line brokerage firm, and
Instinet, a stock trading network, to offer after-hours trading to
small investors misspelled the surname of an analyst who covers
on-line trading at Morgan Stanley Dean Witter. He is Henry M.
McVey, not McVeigh.
</P>
<P>
   BC-TEEN-BUSINESS-CAMP-ART-$ADV08-NYT (moved on Friday, Aug. 6) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Aug. 6,
about a summer business camp for teen-agers in Haverford, Pa.,
misstated the reason for the closing of a similar camp run by
Babson College in Wellesley, Mass. The college decided that its
faculty should concentrate on research and on developing teaching
materials; the cause was not a lack of campers.
</P>
