<HEADER>
A2449 &Cx1f; tic-z
r a BC-MONTINICOL-AZR &LR;      08-18 0662
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MONTINI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SEEING RED IN WHITE MOUNTAINS 
</HEADLINE>
 COL-AZR   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By E.J. MONTINI  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Some residents of Pinetop-Lakeside, Show Low and other
communities in the White Mountains suspect there's something
suspicious going on in the high country of eastern Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   Over the past few months, the area has filled up with strangers,
and a few people wonder if there's more to it than a good tourist
season.
</P>
<P>
   Something evil.
</P>
<P>
   Something tied to the millennium. The Y2K computer problem.
Global chaos. The instillation of a New World Order.
</P>
<P>
   However, like every other wildly apoc alyptic rumor, once a
professional jour nalist spends a few hours investigating the
situation, picking apart the gossip and the hearsay, interviewing
locals, scanning the Internet, he discovers it's actually A LOT
WORSE THAN THEY THINK!!!!
</P>
<P>
   ``Geez,'' said Show Low City Manager Patrick Sherman, ``are you
going to tell me the Russians are coming, the Russians are
coming?''
</P>
<P>
   Of course I'm not.
</P>
<P>
   They're already there. &QL; 
FOREST CAVERNS DESCRIBED
</P>
<P>
   According to a number of concerned citizens telephoning Show
Low's Police Department _ and sending messages over the Internet _
about 1,000 Russian soldiers are hiding in the surrounding for est.
</P>
<P>
   And they're not alone.
</P>
<P>
   One Internet posting says the White Mountains have been hollowed
into ``caverns large enough to house 15,000 elite governmental
politicians, military, rich desirables and modern-day illumi
nati.''
</P>
<P>
   Who'd be foolish enough to believe such outrageous assertions?
When were these caverns supposed to have been dug? And where? And
by whom? And, more importantly, where's my invitation?
</P>
<P>
   Isn't one definition of illuminati an ``Italian-American
journalist with an atti tude problem''?
</P>
<P>
   Officials in Show Low trace the prob lem to this past spring,
when a group of local fire departments printed a pamphlet outlining
an evacuation plan for local res idents.
</P>
<P>
   ``It had to do with forest fires,'' City Manager Sherman says.
``We had a fire danger problem. One fire ate up 4,000 acres. So,
the local departments put out a pamphlet to tell people what to do
in case of a fire.''
</P>
<P>
   Anonymous callers to the Police De partment and Internet
conspiracy buffs see it differently. They figure a ``fire
evacuation'' is only a ruse to get people out of their houses so
weary Russian sol diers can once again enjoy the pleasures of
indoor plumbing. &QL; 
LOOSE SCREWS UNTIGHTENED
</P>
<P>
   Show Low Police Capt. John Jarrett, who's seen the rumors on the
Internet, says, ``It's all ridiculous, completely made up. But
people latch onto it and it grows into secret Russian troops and
poli ticians.''
</P>
<P>
   And space aliens.
</P>
<P>
   You had to figure they were involved somehow.
</P>
<P>
   ``This area (the White Mountains) has been under intense
scrutiny for UFO-re lated reasons,'' one computer message reads.
Another notes flashing lights in the night sky, then poses the
question: ``Is White Mountain housing a new breed of U.S./ NWO (New
World Order) aircraft that is about to be unleashed?''
</P>
<P>
   Sherman believes TV and newspaper reports describing potential
Y2K disasters have untightened some already loose screws.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are people out there who thrive on spreading rumors like
this and making other people paranoid,'' he says. `'The il logic
doesn't matter to them. I mean, are the Russian soldiers and all
these politi cians supposed to live side by side in the caves?''
</P>
<P>
   When you think about it, is that such a bad idea?
</P>
<P>
   Isn't it possible we're looking at this the wrong way _ as a
nuisance rather than an opportunity?
</P>
<P>
   Maybe it's time we quit agonizing over how to prevent 15,000
politicians, mili tary officers, wealthy businessmen and others
from crawling into caves in the White Mountains, and instead asked
our selves:
</P>
<P>
   How do we keep them there? &QL; 
 &QL; 
E.J. Montini can be reached at (602) 444-8978 or at
ed.montini &LR; pni.com. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-18-99 2357EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990818.0424 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 23:57 </DATE_TIME>
